                <fr:anchor>7389</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-018F</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-018F.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Closure of regular languages under complementation">Closure of <fr:link href="jms-017Y.xml" title="Regular language" addr="jms-017Y" type="local">regular languages</fr:link> under complementation</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Corollary</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="jms-017Y.xml" title="Regular language" addr="jms-017Y" type="local">regular language</fr:link> over an <fr:link href="jms-016H.xml" title="Alphabet" addr="jms-016H" type="local">alphabet</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex>, then so is its complement <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ^\star \setminus  L]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>16</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>7388</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6112</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-6112.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-017Y.xml" title="Regular language" addr="jms-017Y" type="local">regular language</fr:link>, and so by <fr:link href="jms-018B.xml" title="Kleene’s theorem" addr="jms-018B" type="local">Kleene’s theorem</fr:link> we have some <fr:link href="jms-017L.xml" title="Deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017L" type="local">DFA</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> satisfying <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L=\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. We define a new <fr:link href="jms-017L.xml" title="Deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017L" type="local">DFA</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lnot {M}]]></fr:tex> satisfying <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (\lnot {M}\right )\mathclose {}} = \Sigma ^\star \setminus  L]]></fr:tex> by setting <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lnot {M}]]></fr:tex> to have the same states, transition function, and starting state as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> but with the opposite set of accepting states:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  F_{\lnot {M}} = Q_{M}\setminus F_{M}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>The desired property of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lnot {M}]]></fr:tex> is immediate.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
